!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

suspicious /səˈspɪʃəs/

1. ADJ If you are suspicious of someone or something, you do not trust them, and are careful when dealing with them. 怀疑的 

例： He was rightly suspicious of meeting me until I reassured him I was not writing about him. 他对于见我充满疑虑，直到我向他再次保证我不是在写有关他的东西。 

2. suspiciously ADJ 怀疑地 [ADV after v] 

例： 'What is it you want me to do?' Adams asked suspiciously. “你要我去干的是什么？”亚当斯怀疑地问道。 

3. ADJ If you are suspicious of someone or something, you believe that they are probably involved in a crime or some dishonest activity. 起疑心的 

例： Two officers on patrol became suspicious of two men in a car. 两位巡警对一辆小汽车内的两名男子起了疑心。 

4. ADJ If you describe someone or something as suspicious , you mean that there is some aspect of them which makes you think that they are involved in a crime or a dishonest activity. 可疑的 

例： He reported that two suspicious-looking characters had approached Callendar. 他报告说两名看似可疑的人曾靠近过卡兰德。 

5. suspiciously ADV 可疑地 

例： They'll question them as to whether anyone was seen acting suspiciously in the area over the last few days. 他们将询问这些人过去几天是否在该地区发现行迹可疑的人。

</div>

